# ── Temple TV Admin — environment variables ───────────────────────────────────
#
# Copy this file to .env.local (git-ignored) and fill in the values for
# your environment. Vite automatically loads .env.local in dev and merges
# it over .env. In CI / Render / Replit you set these as build-time env vars.
#
# IMPORTANT: all VITE_* variables are inlined into the JS bundle at build time.
# Never put secrets (API keys, passwords, JWT secrets) in VITE_* variables —
# they will be shipped to every browser that loads the admin SPA.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# API origin for the admin SPA.
#
# Set this when the admin SPA is served from a different origin than the API
# (e.g. admin.templetv.org.ng hosts the SPA, api.templetv.org.ng hosts the API).
#
# Leave it UNSET (or delete the line) in local dev — Vite's proxy already
# forwards /api → localhost:5000, so the relative same-origin path is correct.
#
# Accepted formats (the trailing slash and /api suffix are both optional):
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.templetv.org.ng
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.templetv.org.ng/api
#
# If this is unset on a production host whose hostname begins with "admin.",
# the app will INFER the API at "api.<rest-of-hostname>" and print a warning
# in the browser console telling you to set this variable explicitly.
#
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.templetv.org.ng
